result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

TRANSCRIPT OF SENTENCING HEARING HELD ON 2/19/15 - JILL  BARTOL, REPORTER
TRANSCRIPT OF STATUS HEARING HELD ON 6/26/14 - JILL BARTOL, REPORTER

Defendant Dale W Neumann in court with attorney Mark D. Lawton.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
14CF29 & 14CF34:
Interpreter Dawn Ruthe sworn.
Atty Hendee states that at the last hearing the defendant waived the Prelim in both matters. Since that hearing; the state has filed the information in both cases.  The parties will be requesting a PSI and setting a sentencing date.  Atty Hendee states what the plea agreement.
Atty Lawton agrees.  Court questions the defendant.  Defendant enters a No Contest plea.
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.   Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.

  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Ct. 1 in 14CF29.  
14CF34 will be dismissed and read-in.
PSI ordered.
Set for Sentencing
bond continued.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for October 31, 2014 at 02:00 pm.
